Package: metahelpers
Type: Package
Title: Convenience Helpers for Three-Level Random-Effects Meta-Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Mohamadjavad", "Ershadmanesh", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "you@example.com")
Description: A thin layer of convenience functions on top of 'metafor' and
    'clubSandwich' for fitting three-level random-effects models (effect sizes
    nested in studies nested in clusters) with cluster-robust (CR2) inference,
    multilevel I-squared, prediction intervals, and tidy result extraction.
    The goal is to remove the boilerplate that surrounds every multilevel
    meta-analysis without hiding the underlying model from the user.
